The paper proposes a framework for entity resolution (ER), which is a task commonly studied in the database community (cs.DB). The framework involves a combination of human and machine efforts, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses optimization approaches for the framework, which involves sampling and precision-recall trade-offs, topics that are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
